cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with information leakage in wiretap channels, which is a topic related to information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the development of algorithms, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.MM (Mathematical Software). Finally, the study of binary symmetric channels and binary erasure channels involves statistical analysis, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
